{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":424,"text":"In Oxford in the 1950s,"},{"time":2286,"text":"there was a fantastic doctor, who was very unusual,"},{"time":6054,"text":"named Alice Stewart."},{"time":8086,"text":"And Alice was unusual partly because, of course,"},{"time":11229,"text":"she was a woman, which was pretty rare in the 1950s."},{"time":14709,"text":"And she was brilliant, she was one of the,"},{"time":16820,"text":"at the time, the youngest Fellow to be elected to the Royal College of Physicians."},{"time":21636,"text":"She was unusual too because she continued to work after she got married,"},{"time":25393,"text":"after she had kids,"},{"time":27488,"text":"and even after she got divorced and was a single parent,"},{"time":30496,"text":"she continued her medical work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32779,"text":"And she was unusual because she was really interested in a new science,"},{"time":36899,"text":"the emerging field of epidemiology,"},{"time":39523,"text":"the study of patterns in disease."},{"time":43011,"text":"But like every scientist, she appreciated"},{"time":45179,"text":"that to make her mark, what she needed to do"},{"time":47435,"text":"was find a hard problem and solve it."},{"time":51953,"text":"The hard problem that Alice chose"},{"time":54497,"text":"was the rising incidence of childhood cancers."},{"time":57895,"text":"Most disease is correlated with poverty,"},{"time":60085,"text":"but in the case of childhood cancers,"},{"time":62354,"text":"the children who were dying seemed mostly to come"},{"time":64958,"text":"from affluent families."},{"time":67403,"text":"So, what, she wanted to know,"},{"time":69146,"text":"could explain this anomaly?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":72228,"text":"Now, Alice had trouble getting funding for her research."},{"time":75011,"text":"In the end, she got just 1,000 pounds"},{"time":77002,"text":"from the Lady Tata Memorial prize."},{"time":79257,"text":"And that meant she knew she only had one shot"},{"time":81800,"text":"at collecting her data."},{"time":83842,"text":"Now, she had no idea what to look for."},{"time":86319,"text":"This really was a needle in a haystack sort of search,"},{"time":89435,"text":"so she asked everything she could think of."},{"time":92057,"text":"Had the children eaten boiled sweets?"},{"time":93890,"text":"Had they consumed colored drinks?"},{"time":95963,"text":"Did they eat fish and chips?"},{"time":97610,"text":"Did they have indoor or outdoor plumbing?"},{"time":99618,"text":"What time of life had they started school?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":103034,"text":"And when her carbon copied questionnaire started to come back,"},{"time":106402,"text":"one thing and one thing only jumped out"},{"time":109322,"text":"with the statistical clarity of a kind that"},{"time":111858,"text":"most scientists can only dream of."},{"time":114698,"text":"By a rate of two to one,"},{"time":116618,"text":"the children who had died"},{"time":118699,"text":"had had mothers who had been X-rayed when pregnant."},{"time":124994,"text":"Now that finding flew in the face of conventional wisdom."},{"time":129499,"text":"Conventional wisdom held"},{"time":131406,"text":"that everything was safe up to a point, a threshold."},{"time":135403,"text":"It flew in the face of conventional wisdom,"},{"time":137730,"text":"which was huge enthusiasm for the cool new technology"},{"time":141188,"text":"of that age, which was the X-ray machine."},{"time":144834,"text":"And it flew in the face of doctors' idea of themselves,"},{"time":149058,"text":"which was as people who helped patients,"},{"time":152866,"text":"they didn't harm them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155562,"text":"Nevertheless, Alice Stewart rushed to publish"},{"time":159250,"text":"her preliminary findings in The Lancet in 1956."},{"time":162834,"text":"People got very excited, there was talk of the Nobel Prize,"},{"time":166842,"text":"and Alice really was in a big hurry"},{"time":168962,"text":"to try to study all the cases of childhood cancer she could find"},{"time":172753,"text":"before they disappeared."},{"time":174906,"text":"In fact, she need not have hurried."},{"time":179250,"text":"It was fully 25 years before the British and medical --"},{"time":183441,"text":"British and American medical establishments"},{"time":186313,"text":"abandoned the practice of X-raying pregnant women."},{"time":192417,"text":"The data was out there, it was open, it was freely available,"},{"time":197898,"text":"but nobody wanted to know."},{"time":202122,"text":"A child a week was dying,"},{"time":204806,"text":"but nothing changed."},{"time":207539,"text":"Openness alone can't drive change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213794,"text":"So for 25 years Alice Stewart had a very big fight on her hands."},{"time":219411,"text":"So, how did she know that she was right?"},{"time":222658,"text":"Well, she had a fantastic model for thinking."},{"time":226321,"text":"She worked with a statistician named George Kneale,"},{"time":228566,"text":"and George was pretty much everything that Alice wasn't."},{"time":230950,"text":"So, Alice was very outgoing and sociable,"},{"time":234019,"text":"and George was a recluse."},{"time":236477,"text":"Alice was very warm, very empathetic with her patients."},{"time":240491,"text":"George frankly preferred numbers to people."},{"time":244530,"text":"But he said this fantastic thing about their working relationship."},{"time":248508,"text":"He said, \"My job is to prove Dr. Stewart wrong.\""},{"time":254844,"text":"He actively sought disconfirmation."},{"time":258401,"text":"Different ways of looking at her models,"},{"time":260738,"text":"at her statistics, different ways of crunching the data"},{"time":263995,"text":"in order to disprove her."},{"time":267058,"text":"He saw his job as creating conflict around her theories."},{"time":272682,"text":"Because it was only by not being able to prove"},{"time":275778,"text":"that she was wrong,"},{"time":278146,"text":"that George could give Alice the confidence she needed"},{"time":281267,"text":"to know that she was right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284249,"text":"It's a fantastic model of collaboration --"},{"time":288924,"text":"thinking partners who aren't echo chambers."},{"time":293931,"text":"I wonder how many of us have,"},{"time":296283,"text":"or dare to have, such collaborators."},{"time":303202,"text":"Alice and George were very good at conflict."},{"time":306979,"text":"They saw it as thinking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310115,"text":"So what does that kind of constructive conflict require?"},{"time":314388,"text":"Well, first of all, it requires that we find people"},{"time":317763,"text":"who are very different from ourselves."},{"time":320411,"text":"That means we have to resist the neurobiological drive,"},{"time":324747,"text":"which means that we really prefer people mostly like ourselves,"},{"time":329251,"text":"and it means we have to seek out people"},{"time":331475,"text":"with different backgrounds, different disciplines,"},{"time":333947,"text":"different ways of thinking and different experience,"},{"time":338098,"text":"and find ways to engage with them."},{"time":341963,"text":"That requires a lot of patience and a lot of energy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346607,"text":"And the more I've thought about this,"},{"time":348418,"text":"the more I think, really, that that's a kind of love."},{"time":353579,"text":"Because you simply won't commit that kind of energy"},{"time":356648,"text":"and time if you don't really care."},{"time":361339,"text":"And it also means that we have to be prepared to change our minds."},{"time":365799,"text":"Alice's daughter told me"},{"time":368163,"text":"that every time Alice went head-to-head with a fellow scientist,"},{"time":371275,"text":"they made her think and think and think again."},{"time":375459,"text":"\"My mother,\" she said, \"My mother didn't enjoy a fight,"},{"time":379477,"text":"but she was really good at them.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":384619,"text":"So it's one thing to do that in a one-to-one relationship."},{"time":388789,"text":"But it strikes me that the biggest problems we face,"},{"time":392076,"text":"many of the biggest disasters that we've experienced,"},{"time":394950,"text":"mostly haven't come from individuals,"},{"time":396901,"text":"they've come from organizations,"},{"time":398789,"text":"some of them bigger than countries,"},{"time":400797,"text":"many of them capable of affecting hundreds,"},{"time":403057,"text":"thousands, even millions of lives."},{"time":407060,"text":"So how do organizations think?"},{"time":411498,"text":"Well, for the most part, they don't."},{"time":415524,"text":"And that isn't because they don't want to,"},{"time":418517,"text":"it's really because they can't."},{"time":420922,"text":"And they can't because the people inside of them"},{"time":424269,"text":"are too afraid of conflict."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428477,"text":"In surveys of European and American executives,"},{"time":431341,"text":"fully 85 percent of them acknowledged"},{"time":434311,"text":"that they had issues or concerns at work"},{"time":437828,"text":"that they were afraid to raise."},{"time":441461,"text":"Afraid of the conflict that that would provoke,"},{"time":444620,"text":"afraid to get embroiled in arguments"},{"time":446988,"text":"that they did not know how to manage,"},{"time":449019,"text":"and felt that they were bound to lose."},{"time":453596,"text":"Eighty-five percent is a really big number."},{"time":459773,"text":"It means that organizations mostly can't do"},{"time":462588,"text":"what George and Alice so triumphantly did."},{"time":464916,"text":"They can't think together."},{"time":469315,"text":"And it means that people like many of us,"},{"time":471556,"text":"who have run organizations,"},{"time":473740,"text":"and gone out of our way to try to find the very best people we can,"},{"time":477307,"text":"mostly fail to get the best out of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483580,"text":"So how do we develop the skills that we need?"},{"time":486916,"text":"Because it does take skill and practice, too."},{"time":490999,"text":"If we aren't going to be afraid of conflict,"},{"time":494413,"text":"we have to see it as thinking,"},{"time":496572,"text":"and then we have to get really good at it."},{"time":500908,"text":"So, recently, I worked with an executive named Joe,"},{"time":505172,"text":"and Joe worked for a medical device company."},{"time":508644,"text":"And Joe was very worried about the device that he was working on."},{"time":511619,"text":"He thought that it was too complicated"},{"time":514644,"text":"and he thought that its complexity"},{"time":516508,"text":"created margins of error that could really hurt people."},{"time":520775,"text":"He was afraid of doing damage to the patients he was trying to help."},{"time":524915,"text":"But when he looked around his organization,"},{"time":527220,"text":"nobody else seemed to be at all worried."},{"time":531681,"text":"So, he didn't really want to say anything."},{"time":534236,"text":"After all, maybe they knew something he didn't."},{"time":536420,"text":"Maybe he'd look stupid."},{"time":539004,"text":"But he kept worrying about it,"},{"time":541210,"text":"and he worried about it so much that he got to the point"},{"time":544256,"text":"where he thought the only thing he could do"},{"time":546415,"text":"was leave a job he loved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550545,"text":"In the end, Joe and I found a way"},{"time":554545,"text":"for him to raise his concerns."},{"time":556400,"text":"And what happened then is what almost always"},{"time":559271,"text":"happens in this situation."},{"time":560865,"text":"It turned out everybody had exactly the same"},{"time":564086,"text":"questions and doubts."},{"time":565832,"text":"So now Joe had allies. They could think together."},{"time":569864,"text":"And yes, there was a lot of conflict and debate"},{"time":573128,"text":"and argument, but that allowed everyone around the table"},{"time":577432,"text":"to be creative, to solve the problem,"},{"time":581512,"text":"and to change the device."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585840,"text":"Joe was what a lot of people might think of"},{"time":589216,"text":"as a whistle-blower,"},{"time":591488,"text":"except that like almost all whistle-blowers,"},{"time":594203,"text":"he wasn't a crank at all,"},{"time":596576,"text":"he was passionately devoted to the organization"},{"time":600024,"text":"and the higher purposes that that organization served."},{"time":603472,"text":"But he had been so afraid of conflict,"},{"time":607288,"text":"until finally he became more afraid of the silence."},{"time":612368,"text":"And when he dared to speak,"},{"time":614227,"text":"he discovered much more inside himself"},{"time":617625,"text":"and much more give in the system than he had ever imagined."},{"time":622867,"text":"And his colleagues don't think of him as a crank."},{"time":626198,"text":"They think of him as a leader."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631326,"text":"So, how do we have these conversations more easily"},{"time":635694,"text":"and more often?"},{"time":637607,"text":"Well, the University of Delft"},{"time":639593,"text":"requires that its PhD students"},{"time":641990,"text":"have to submit five statements that they're prepared to defend."},{"time":645903,"text":"It doesn't really matter what the statements are about,"},{"time":649287,"text":"what matters is that the candidates are willing and able"},{"time":653079,"text":"to stand up to authority."},{"time":655682,"text":"I think it's a fantastic system,"},{"time":658046,"text":"but I think leaving it to PhD candidates"},{"time":660559,"text":"is far too few people, and way too late in life."},{"time":664864,"text":"I think we need to be teaching these skills"},{"time":668030,"text":"to kids and adults at every stage of their development,"},{"time":672110,"text":"if we want to have thinking organizations"},{"time":674559,"text":"and a thinking society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678206,"text":"The fact is that most of the biggest catastrophes that we've witnessed"},{"time":683824,"text":"rarely come from information that is secret or hidden."},{"time":690215,"text":"It comes from information that is freely available and out there,"},{"time":694519,"text":"but that we are willfully blind to,"},{"time":696903,"text":"because we can't handle, don't want to handle,"},{"time":700031,"text":"the conflict that it provokes."},{"time":704438,"text":"But when we dare to break that silence,"},{"time":707367,"text":"or when we dare to see,"},{"time":710024,"text":"and we create conflict,"},{"time":712279,"text":"we enable ourselves and the people around us"},{"time":714904,"text":"to do our very best thinking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719150,"text":"Open information is fantastic,"},{"time":722526,"text":"open networks are essential."},{"time":725710,"text":"But the truth won't set us free"},{"time":727687,"text":"until we develop the skills and the habit and the talent"},{"time":731451,"text":"and the moral courage to use it."},{"time":735588,"text":"Openness isn't the end."},{"time":739348,"text":"It's the beginning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741990,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}